title: Exposing response headers for the current xhr codebase.
body:
feat($resource,$xhr): make HTTP headers available to $xhr and $resource callbacks

- $browser.xhr exposes headers function for retrieving one or all headers
- $xhr service exposes the headers function to both success and error callbacks
- $resource service exposes the headers function in all of its callbacks

feat:$xhr: provide access to $xhr header defaults
body:
$xhr header defaults are now exposed as $xhr.defaults.headers.common and
$xhr.default.headers.<httpmethod>. This allows applications to configure
their defaults as needed.

This commit doesn't allow headers to be set per request, only per
application. Per request change would require api change, which I tried
to avoid *for now*.
